import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for series, group in data.groupby('Series'):
        ax.scatter(group['X'], group['Y'], label=series)
    ax.set_xlabel('X')
    ax.set_ylabel('Y')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['X'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.axvline(data['X'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['X'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.boxplot(x='Series', y='X', data=data)

    plt.ylabel('X')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='Y', by='Series', ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Series and Y?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Series')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend(title='Series', loc='upper right')
    return plt;
